verses.text: And the whole congregation of the children of Israel assembled together at Shiloh , and set up the tabernacle of the congregation there. And the land was subdued before them. \p
And there remained among the children of Israel seven tribes , which had not yet received their inheritance.
And Joshua said unto the children of Israel , How long \add are\add* ye slack to go to possess the land , which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God of your fathers hath given you?

Give out from among you three men for \add each\add* tribe : and I will send them, and they shall rise , and go through the land , and describe it according to the inheritance of them; and they shall come \add again\add* to me.
And they shall divide it into seven parts : Judah shall abide in their coast on the south , and the house of Joseph shall abide in their coasts on the north.

Ye shall therefore describe the land \add into\add* seven parts , and bring \add the description\add* hither to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our God.

But the Levites have no part among you; for the priesthood of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \add is\add* their inheritance : and Gad , and Reuben , and half the tribe of Manasseh , have received their inheritance beyond Jordan on the east , which Moses the servant of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* gave them. \p

¶ And the men arose , and went away : and Joshua charged them that went to describe the land , saying , Go and walk through the land , and describe it, and come again to me, that I may here cast lots for you before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in Shiloh.
And the men went and passed through the land , and described it by cities into seven parts in a book , and came \add again\add* to Joshua to the host at Shiloh. \p
¶ And Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: and there Joshua divided the land unto the children of Israel according to their divisions. \p
¶ And the lot of the tribe of the children of Benjamin came up according to their families : and the coast of their lot came forth between the children of Judah and the children of Joseph.

And their border on the north side was from Jordan ; and the border went up to the side of Jericho on the north side, and went up through the mountains westward ; and the goings out thereof were at the wilderness of Beth-aven.

And the border went over from thence toward Luz , to the side of Luz , which \add is\add* Beth-el , southward ; and the border descended to Ataroth-adar , near the hill that \add lieth\add* on the south side of the nether Beth-horon.

And the border was drawn \add thence\add*, and compassed the corner of the sea southward , from the hill that \add lieth\add* before Beth-horon southward ; and the goings out thereof were at Kirjath-baal , which \add is\add* Kirjath-jearim , a city of the children of Judah : this \add was\add* the west quarter.
And the south quarter \add was\add* from the end of Kirjath-jearim , and the border went out on the west , and went out to the well of waters of Nephtoah :

And the border came down to the end of the mountain that \add lieth\add* before the valley of the son of Hinnom , \add and\add* which \add is\add* in the valley of the giants on the north , and descended to the valley of Hinnom , to the side of Jebusi on the south , and descended to En-rogel ,

And was drawn from the north , and went forth to En-shemesh , and went forth toward Geliloth , which \add is\add* over against the going up of Adummim , and descended to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben ,
And passed along toward the side over against Arabah northward , and went down unto Arabah :\f + \fr 18.18 \ft Arabah: or, the plain\f*

And the border passed along to the side of Beth-hoglah northward : and the outgoings of the border were at the north bay of the salt sea at the south end of Jordan : this \add was\add* the south coast.\f + \fr 18.19 \ft bay: Heb. tongue\f*
And Jordan was the border of it on the east side. This \add was\add* the inheritance of the children of Benjamin , by the coasts thereof round about , according to their families.
Now the cities of the tribe of the children of Benjamin according to their families were Jericho , and Beth-hoglah , and the valley of Keziz ,
And Beth-arabah , and Zemaraim , and Beth-el ,
And Avim , and Parah , and Ophrah ,
And Chephar-haammonai , and Ophni , and Gaba ; twelve cities with their villages :
Gibeon , and Ramah , and Beeroth ,
And Mizpeh , and Chephirah , and Mozah ,
And Rekem , and Irpeel , and Taralah ,

And Zelah , Eleph , and Jebusi , which \add is\add* Jerusalem , Gibeath , \add and\add* Kirjath ; fourteen cities with their villages. This \add is\add* the inheritance of the children of Benjamin according to their families.
